ague]]|manager15=[[Pat Kelly (catcher)|Pat Kelly]] and [[Mel Queen (pitcher/outfielder)|Mel Queen]]\n|level16=[[Double-A (baseball)|AA]]|team16=[[Tennessee Smokies]]|league16=[[Southern League (baseball)|Southern League]]|manager16=[[Rocket Wheeler]]\n|level17=[[Single-A (baseball)|A]]  |team17=[[Dunedin Blue Jays]]|league17=[[Florida State League]]|manager17=[[Marty Pevey]]\n|level18=[[Single-A (baseball)|A]]|team18=[[Hagerstown Suns]]|league18=[[South Atlantic League]]|manager18=[[Rolando Pino]]\n|level19=[[Class A-Short Season|A-Short Season]]|team19=[[Queens Kings]]|league19=[[New York\u2013Penn League]]|manager19=[[Eddie Rodr\u00edguez]]\n|level20=[[Rookie League|Rookie]]|team20=[[Medicine Hat Blue Jays]]|league20=[[Pioneer League (baseball)|Pioneer League]]|manager20=[[Paul Elliott (baseball)|Paul Elliott]]}}<ref>Johnson, Lloyd, and Wolff, Miles, ed., ''The Encyclopedia of Minor League Baseball'', 3rd edition. Durham, North Carolina: Baseball America, 2007</ref>\n\n==References==\n<references/>\n\n==External links==\n*[https://www.baseball-reference.com/teams/TOR/2000.shtml 2000 Toronto Blue Jays] at ''Baseball Reference''\n*[http://baseball-almanac.com/teamstats/roster.php?y=2000&t=TOR 2000 Toronto Blue Jays] at ''Baseball Almanac''\n\n{{2000 MLB season by team}}\n{{Toronto Blue Jays}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:2000 Toronto Blue Jays Season}}\n[[Category:Toronto Blue Jays seasons]]\n[[Category:2000 Major League Baseball season|Toronto Blue Jays season]]\n[[Category:2000 in Canadian sports]]\n[[Category:2000 in Toronto]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use mdy dates|date=November 2013}}\n{{Infobox MLB yearly\n| name = Toronto Blue Jays\n| season = 2000\n| misc =\n| logo =\n| current league = American League\n| y1 = 1977\n| division = [[American League East|East Division]]\n| y2 = 1977\n| Uniform logo =\n| ballpark = [[SkyDome]]\n| y4 = 1989\n| city = [[Toronto]]\n| y5 = 1977\n| record         = 83\u201379 (.512)\n| divisional place = 3rd\n| owners = [[Rogers Communications]], [[Interbrew]]\n| general managers = [[Gord Ash]]\n| managers = [[Jim Fregosi]]\n| television = [[CBC Television]]<br>([[Brian Williams (sportscaster)|Brian Williams]], [[Rich Waltz]], [[John Cerutti]])<br>[[The Sports Network]]<br>([[Dan Shulman]], [[Buck Martinez]])<br>[[Rogers Sportsnet|CTV Sportsnet]]<br>([[Rod Black]], [[Joe Carter]])\n| radio = [[CHUM (AM)]]<br>([[Jerry Howarth]], [[Tom Cheek]], [[Gary Matthews]])\n|}}\nThe '''2000 [[Toronto Blue Jays]]''' season was the franchise's 24th season of [[Major League Baseball]]. It resulted in the Blue Jays finishing third in the [[American League]] East with a record of 83 wins and 79 losses. It is the team's first season with new mascots [[Toronto Blue Jays mascots|Ace]] and [[Toronto Blue Jays mascots|Diamond]].\n\n==Offseason==\n* November 8, 1999: [[Ra\u00fal Mondes\u00ed]] was traded by the Los Angeles Dodgers with Pedro Borb\u00f3n to the Toronto Blue Jays for Shawn Green and Jorge Nunez (minors).<ref>[https://www.baseball-reference.com/m/mondera01.shtml Ra\u00fal Mondes\u00ed Statistics] Baseball-Reference.com</ref>\n*November 11, 1999: Paul Spoljaric was traded by the Toronto Blue Jays with Pat Hentgen to the St. Louis Cardinals for Alberto Castillo, Matt DeWitt, and Lance Painter.<ref>[https://www.baseball-reference.com/s/spoljpa01.shtml Paul Spoljaric Statistics] Baseball-Reference.com</ref>\nDecember 13, 1999: DeWayne Wise was drafted by the Toronto Blue Jays from the Cincinnati Reds in the 1999 rule 5 draft.<ref>https://www.baseball-reference.com/players/w/wisede01.shtml</ref>\n\n==Regular season==\n\n===Season standings===\n{{2000 AL East standings|highlight=Toronto Blue Jays}}\n\n===Record vs. opponents===\n{{2000 AL Record vs. opponents|team=TOR}}\n\n===Notable transactions===\nJuly 19, 2000: [[Esteban Loaiza]] was traded by the Texas Rangers to the Toronto Blue Jays for Darwin Cubill\u00e1n and Michael Young.<ref>[https://www.baseball-reference.com/l/loaizes01.shtml Esteban Loaiza Statistics] Baseball-Reference.com</ref>\n*July 26, 2000: [[Rob Ducey]] was traded by the Philadelphia Phillies to the Toronto Blue Jays for a player to be named later. <ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.baseball-reference.com/players/d/duceyro01.shtml |title= Rob Ducey: Career Statistics |publisher= Baseball Reference| accessdate= 14 March 2018}}</ref>\n\n===2000 Draft picks===\n''Source'' <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.baseball-reference.com/draft/index.cgi?team_ID=TOR&year_ID=2000&draft_type=junreg&query_type=franch_year|title=Feature: 2000 Free Agent Draft Pick Compensation |work=[[Baseball-Reference.com]] |accessdate=September 2, 2014}}</ref>\n\nThe [[2001 Major League Baseball draft|2002 MLB draft]] was held in June 2001.\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size: 95%; text-align: center;\"\n|-\n! style=\"background:#005ac0;\" color:white;\"| <span style=\"color:white;\">Round</span>\n! style=\"background:#005ac0;\" color:white;\"| <span style=\"color:white;\">Pick</span>\n! style=\"background:#005ac0;\" color:white;\"| <span style=\"color:white;\">Player</span>\n! style=\"background:#005ac0;\" color:white;\"| <span style=\"color:white;\">Position</span>\n! style=\"background:#005ac0;\" color:white;\"| <span style=\"color:white;\">College/School</span>\n! style=\"background:#005ac0;\" color:white;\"| <span style=\"color:white;\">Nationality</span>\n|-\n!width=\"65\"|\n!width=\"45\"|\n! style=\"width:150px;\"|\n!width=\"60\"|\n! style=\"width:250px;\"|\n! style=\"width:100px;\"|\n|-\n| 1\n| 18\n| Miguel Negron\n| OF\n| Manuela Toro High School ([[Caguas, Puerto Rico|Caguas, PR]])\n| {{flagicon|Puerto Rico}}\n|-\n| 1s\n| 33\n| [[Dustin McGowan]]\n| RHP\n| [[Long County High School]]\n| {{flagicon|United States}}\n|-\n| 2\n| 45\n| Peter Bauer\n| RHP\n| [[University of South Carolina]]\n| {{flagicon|United States}}\n|-\n| 2\n| 58\n| Dominic Rich\n| 2B\n| [[Auburn University]]\n| {{flagicon|United States}}\n|-\n| 3\n| 88\n| Morrin Davis\n| OF\n| [[Hillsborough High School (Tampa, Florida)